<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - CYLINDER HEAD AND VALVES - CYLINDER HEAD RECONDITIONING -
        VALVE ROTATORS
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="2">
        <title>VALVE ROTATORS</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>CLEANING</title>
            <para>Clean rotators in a clean solvent.</para>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>INSPECTION</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To properly test the rotator for function, a valve spring load must be applied to the
                    rotator.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>The rotator must be lubricated with clean engine oil prior to testing.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the valve spring with the rotator in the spring tester
                    <emph type="bold">ZTSE2241</emph>. Place a ball bearing between the rotator and ram of the spring
                    tester. The ball bearing must be large enough to prevent the ram from touching any part of the
                    rotator.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Paint a reference line on the rotator.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Compress the valve spring rapidly with even pressure and observe the rotator as it
                    turns. (Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050451">4.51</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Replace any rotator which does
                    <emph type="bold">NOT</emph>
                    turn.
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1050450" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11150" filename="../figcg1/CG11150.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.50.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Scale</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Valve Spring</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. Load Indicator</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1050451" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg10654" filename="../figcg1/CG10654.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.51.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
